cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel probabilistic inference framework for reinforcement learning that utilises a parametrised action-value function to summarise future dynamics of the underlying MDP. This is a core machine learning problem and hence, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI and hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): Reinforcement learning is also a subfield of control theory and hence, cs.SY is a possible sub-category.
4. cs.RO (Robotics): Reinforcement learning is widely used in robotics and hence, cs.RO is also a possible sub-category.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a family of actor-critic methods and hence, cs.DS is a possible sub-category.
